{
  "text": "Accurate detection of citrus the HLB-associated bacterium can be challenging because of their low titers and uneven distribution within the infected plants [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Current real-time PCR methods target LasA I gene of CLas prophage genes [CITATION_3] . The LasA I gene contained 12 nearly identical tandem repeat (NITRs) 132 bp in length and 4 partial repeats [CITATION_4] . When compared with conventional 16S rDNA-based real-time PCR, targeting the repeat sequence reduced the relative detectable threshold by approximately 9 and 3 real-time PCR cycles for LasA I gene [CITATION_5] .",
  "correct_citation": {
